Murang a county has launched a Quick Response Police Unit following several clashes between political leaders in public meetings.County commissioner John Elungata said the unit will assist police in tightening security. The commissioner said the team is drawn from all subcounties. It will have a central commander at the county headquarters.Elungata said the unit is a tactical team that has been adequately trained to rapidly deal with incidents. These officers have been trained to operate under difficult situations, he said.The county commissioner said the team will quell unrests in political rallies that turn chaotic. I wondered why the situation has stretched this far yet we have trained officers to handle such incidents, Elungata said. The county has witnessed several clashes between Governor Mwangi Wairia and Kigumo MP Jamleck Kamau, who has declared his interest to unseat Wairia.